<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1865-03-29T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1865-03-29T00:00:00-05:00" n="193" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d193">
                        <head><persName type="from">Mr. Seward</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr.
                                Burnley</persName></head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State,</hi>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington,</hi></placeName>
                                <date calendar="gregorian" when="1865-03-29"><hi rend="italic">March</hi> 29, 1865.</date></dateline></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir:</hi> I have the honor to acknowledge the
                            receipt of your note of the 26th instant, informing me that Mr. Home had
                            been instructed to report to her Majesty’s government how soon it would
                            be possible for him and his colleague from the government to close the
                            fishery commission as established by the treaty.</p>
                        <p>I have the honor to be, with the highest consideration, sir, your
                            obedient servant,</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>WILLIAM H. SEWARD.</signed></closer>
                        <postscript>
                            <p>J. <hi rend="smallcaps">Hume Burnley,</hi> Esq., <hi rend="italic">&amp;c., &amp;c., &amp;c</hi>.</p>
                        </postscript>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>